  "prompt": "Is \"why you went there?\" proper grammar?",
  "response": "No, \"why you went there?\" is not proper grammar. It's missing a word that makes it a proper question. Here are some ways to correct it:\n\n*   **Why did you go there?** (This is a direct question.)\n*   **I wonder why you went there.** (This is part of a larger sentence, expressing curiosity.)\n*   **Do you know why you went there?** (Similar to the above, but a direct question about knowledge.)\n*   **The reason why you went there is...** (Starting a sentence to explain the reason.)\n\nThe issue is that \"why you went there\" acts like a noun phrase (a statement of fact, even though it's about a reason), not a question. To make it a question, you need to invert the subject and auxiliary verb (\"did you go\").\n",
